      <div class="msgContentFrame">I'm coming from FFXI where I was a not-so-bad RDM player.  I'm well aware that THM is not XIV's equivalent to a Red Mage, but I picked it up because I liked being a party support caster.  However, THM is frustrating me all to hell in party situations, mainly due to hate control and (mostly) targeting. <br /> <br />Hate - It seems that anytime I do more than one action in a sequence (ie Slow then Banish), I pull hate away from the Gladiator, and start getting nailed.  This wouldn't be a huge issue if Punishing Barbs didn't wear off so quick.  But it seems like I'm spending the majority of my time face down, which makes me more than a little useless. <br /> <br />Targeting - I've been trying to keep silent about gameplay issues with XIV (there's enough people bitching in General, I don't need to add to it) but seriously...  What the hell?  Healing a single party member in a hurry is near impossible.  Tabbing through targets takes a ridiculous amount of time, especially in populated areas.  By the time I finally settle on a target and hit Sacrifice, the party member is usually dead.  The narrow-seeming cone of effect on my spells doesn't help matters either.   <br /> <br />An LS-mate pointed out the use of the F12 key to cycle through party members, which kinda helps a little, but seems to require that I completely drop my current target in order for it to work.  It also doesn't help with targeting the mob that my party is currently fighting.  There doesn't seem to be any /assist command that i've been able to find. <br /> <br />These issues combined with an overall feeling of useless-ness have had me considering changing to another job.  I'm the only THM in our group right now though, and I very much enjoyed the support role in XI.  I'm hoping there's something I can change so that the job is more enjoyable. <br /> <br />Does anybody have any suggestions?  Are there commands I've missed somewhere?  Is spellcasting in XIV just broken?  Do I just plain suck that bad? <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Aolean Mode - Thaumaturge of Mysidia <br /> <br />Ellenzar - Ramuh (Retired)   75 Red Mage    75 Blue Mage</div></div>
