      <div class="msgContentFrame">THM 17 here...and counter-intuitive as it seems, I've found that the easiest way to do this is to simply engage the mob. <br /> <br />Engage, and then situate myself close enough to the melees that the aoe cure hits everyone.  This has two benefits: one, Sacrifice won't leave me out of HP, and 2, if I don't need to cure I can cast something on the mob.   <br /> <br />hate is very wonky though, and very random.  I've pulled hate right after provoke, but I've also seen the lancer in a party I was in -- lowest lv there - pull hate just by engaging the mob.   <br /> <br />I'm not so squishy that I die terribly fast, but it has happened when pulling hate on tougher mobs -.-;<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Aquilla <br /> <br />   75blm 75mnk 75nin 75bst <br />    **Balkanska Mafia!** <br />       LS: WitchesBrew <br />           <br />Zachiel wrote: <br />Black Mages and manaburns are not too strong, you just suck.</div></div>
