      <div class="msgContentFrame">The Thaum cone is larger than it seems. I've spent a long long time healing my PUG and MAR trio partners while they beat on things, there are only a couple AoEs that I get hit by.  <br /> <br />A few notes on hate, once you get Silhouette it cools off a little bit, since in a party I can't spam Phantom Dart anyway I use Silhouette whenever I'm going to attack. Our PUG usually saves his taunt/voke for after I engage, it seems to work better than just taunting right at the start. Consider using single target cure/sacrifices to mitigate enmity generation, you get a lot more hate for using those AoEs. Slow is a huge boon in any fight where you are worried about TP spam, but it has a short duration. I start casting slow when our danger target is at about 60%, as they tend to spam TP moves under 50%.  <br /> <br />If you have any other questions feel free to ask, I've taken Thaum to 20 almost entirely in parties and have been keeping a very close eye on what works and what doesn't in terms of enmity generation, stat allocation, and numbers in general.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Venkelos Ilsevet of Figaro <br />Leader of Invictus, send me a tell if you are interested in joining! <br /></div></div>
